WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:10.920
[Amit Varma]: What makes for a good Indian? What are the duties of a good citizen? We know that the

00:00:10.920 --> 00:00:15.480
[Amit Varma]: relationship between the state and society is dysfunctional, but can it be repaired by

00:00:15.480 --> 00:00:20.880
[Amit Varma]: the actions of committed civilians? Can we rise out of our apathy and make our democracy

00:00:20.880 --> 00:00:27.000
[Amit Varma]: meaningful? We already have a democracy that is of the people and for the people, but can

00:00:27.000 --> 00:00:32.520
[Amit Varma]: it also be by the people?

00:00:32.520 --> 00:00:37.920
[Unknown]: Welcome to the Scene and the Unseen, our weekly podcast on economics, politics and behavioral

00:00:37.920 --> 00:00:43.640
[Unknown]: science. Please welcome your host, Amit Badma.

00:00:43.640 --> 00:00:48.360
[Amit Varma]: Welcome to the Scene and the Unseen. For many months now, I've been wanting to get Ashwin

00:00:48.360 --> 00:00:54.720
[Amit Varma]: Mahesh on the show. Ashwin is a polymath thinker who is an expert on various areas of policy

00:00:54.720 --> 00:01:00.040
[Amit Varma]: such as urban governance, and he's also a civic activist who has participated in politics.

00:01:00.040 --> 00:01:05.120
[Amit Varma]: He was one of the catalysts of the India Against Corruption movement almost a decade ago when

00:01:05.120 --> 00:01:10.760
[Amit Varma]: he was part of J.P. Narayan's Lok Satta movement. He is today in the Aam Aadmi Party and I first

00:01:10.760 --> 00:01:16.120
[Amit Varma]: met him a couple of years ago at a farmer's meeting in Deolali, where I also interviewed

00:01:16.120 --> 00:01:21.160
[Amit Varma]: the Shetkari Sangatana leader Gunwant Patil for what became episode 86 of the Scene and

00:01:21.160 --> 00:01:26.960
[Amit Varma]: the Unseen, my only Hindi episode so far. I had long conversations with Ashwin at Deolali

00:01:26.960 --> 00:01:31.960
[Amit Varma]: and was blown away by the depth of his thinking and the range of his insights. When I invited

00:01:31.960 --> 00:01:36.680
[Amit Varma]: him to appear on the show, among the topics I had in mind were the India Against Corruption

00:01:36.680 --> 00:01:42.200
[Amit Varma]: movement as well as urban governance in general. Ashwin then suggested that we speak about

00:01:42.200 --> 00:01:48.360
[Amit Varma]: participatory democracy, or what he called government by the people. We recorded on January

00:01:48.360 --> 00:01:55.360
[Amit Varma]: 24, 2020, and had a wide-ranging conversation that covered IAC, urban governance, what makes

00:01:55.360 --> 00:02:00.800
[Amit Varma]: a good Indian, the evolution of the Aam Aadmi Party, and many, many other subjects. This

00:02:00.800 --> 00:02:06.840
[Amit Varma]: was one of my most thought-provoking conversations, partly because it ranged over so many subjects

00:02:06.840 --> 00:02:11.100
[Amit Varma]: that even finding a title for this episode became difficult. I hope you'll enjoy it as

00:02:11.100 --> 00:02:19.280
[Amit Varma]: much as I did. But before we get to the episode, let's take a quick commercial break.

